<link href="adcp.css" rel="stylesheet"><entry><xh5>long head • short head</xh5><p> <i>long head</i>—(coll.) capacity for calculation and foresight: He has always had luck, and he has a <u>long head</u> too.</p><p> <i>short head—</i>a narrow margin in victory <i>(originally of horse races): </i>A photo finish was predicted by polls. The final one showed M. Mitered winning by a <u>short head</u>.</p> </entry>
